Sentencas: By this work, we discussed about the fabrication and characterization of tubular anode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) which include nanocomposite powder preparation and analysis.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC

Sentencas: For the synthesis of the Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 nanocomposite powder, the economic synthesis technique known as nitrate-fuel combustion method was used.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC

Sentencas: The NiO-SDC composite was realized by the phase inversion slurry and ball milling techniques.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC

Sentencas: The calcined powder was fully crystalline with mesopores in Sm doped Ceria (SDC) phase.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC

Sentencas: The phase inversion method via dip coating as a simple manufacturing process was adopted to fabricate the Ni-SDC tubes.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC

Sentencas: The sintered tubes exhibited uniform sponge-like porous geometry, with gradual changes in pore size represented as two different zones across the tube.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC

Sentencas: The sintered tubes possess 25%-30% of porosity, a bending strength of 491 +/- 54 MPa and the electrical conductivity in the range of 21-36 Scm(-1) at 500 degrees C-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC

Sentencas: The increase in porosity and reduction in mechanical strength of the tubes after reduction treatment was discussed.
Titulo: Evaluation of microstructural and electrical properties of tubular Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite anode for SOFC
